    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-07T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.114/172</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-07T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 26, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d206fn1">Not printed.</note> The
                    Department is informed that the British Government has neither participated in
                    nor given its official countenance to the negotiations between the Chinese
                    Government and the opium combine but, on the contrary, highly disapproves of the
                    transaction which it hopes the Chinese Government may yet be persuaded to
                    abandon. The Department sincerely regrets that the <pb facs="0324" n="212"
                        xml:id="pg_212"/> information it has received makes it plain that the plan
                    in contemplation for the disposition of opium stocks is in contravention of the
                    spirit of the Hague draft treaty ratified by the United States and China and
                    jeopardizes all the beneficial results that have been accomplished, at so much
                    sacrifice, towards the suppression of the opium traffic. You will therefore make
                    earnest representations to the Chinese Government in this sense, cooperating as
                    closely as possible with your British colleague.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
